@@GHISTORY@@W

The Kinetimancer synthesis arose from a collision between two traditions
that spent centuries in philosophical opposition. The Entropy Scholars --
predecessors of the Necromancer path -- held that understanding dissolution
was fundamental to understanding existence; the Egomancer lineage within
the Psionicist academies held that pure mental will could override any
entropic tendency if properly refined. The structural similarity beneath
that opposition went unnoticed until a small independent order, the Kinetic
Formulists, documented it in the pre-Compact period: both traditions were
working with momentum -- one redirecting the momentum of decay, the other
redirecting the momentum of imposed intent. Their manuscripts were reviewed
by the Violet Compact's registry scholars upon the Compact's founding, who
classified the convergence as dangerous theoretical synthesis and logged its
practitioners under a new registry term -- Kinetimancer. That bureaucratic
label became the tradition's name, carried forward by practitioners who
found the Compact's unease to be confirmation enough.

@@GKINETIMANCER@@W

Kinetimancers are the union of @@GNecromancer@@W entropy and @@mEgomancer@@W will,
engineers of unseen force who bend shadow, poison, and mind-pressure into a
single predictive combat style. They do not simply cast spells—they re-route
momentum and collapse enemy plans before impact.

To become a Kinetimancer, you follow the adept path tied to @@GNecromancer@@W
and @@mEgomancer@@W remort progression.

@@GPassive class advantages@@W
Kinetimancer gains passive scaling through adept levels:

  1) @@wRemort/Adept non-physical spell damage bonus@@W
     - Non-physical remort/adept damage effects gain a passive Kinetimancer
       multiplier.
     - Scaling: +2% damage per Kinetimancer adept level (up to +40% at 20).

@@GUnique Kinetimancer mechanics@@W
  * @@wMagi stance@@W is available on the adept path (shared caster stance with
    either-class access, multi-cast support, dual-cast support, and no-hit
    casting posture).
  * @@wKinetic Reversion@@W is learned at Kinetimancer level 2.
  * Kinetimancer contributes to the @@wMental Power@@W progression family.
  * Kinetimancer uses @@wIntelligence@@W as its adept prime attribute and follows
    a high-mana caster growth profile.

@@GKinetimancer reincarnation bonuses@@W
Each Kinetimancer adept reincarnation grants additional passive scaling:

  * @@wShadow / poison / mental damage@@W: +2% per Kinetimancer adept
    reincarnation.

In short: Kinetimancer is the control-burst adept for dark and psychic realms,
rewarding players who maintain pressure through layered non-physical damage.

